      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-bootstrap-llm"
        },
        "markdown": "## Example first graph request\n\nAfter the handshake, ask for a very small declaration-first graph. For example:\n\n```text\nCreate a small Twilite graph about why dragons would make terrible apartment pets.\n\nUse a declaration node, a reader port exposed by the declaration, 4 or 5 markdown nodes, and reference edges.\nMake the graph funny, readable, and easy to follow.\nKeep it declaration-first and valid.\n```\n\nThe important part is the order: declaration first, then the exposed reader surface, then the content. Add a portal only when something needs to target an exposed surface.",
        "_placement": {
          "version": 1,
          "state": "manually-shaped",
          "source": "manual",
          "updatedAt": 1781133193828,
          "reason": "node-drag"
        }
      }
    },
